README:
The energetic costs of the human connectome
===============

[#Preprint](https://www.biorxiv.org/content/10.1101/2023.04.25.538209v1)

This dataset consists of quantitative FDG-PET, BOLD-fMRI, and DWI data from 20 right-handed, healthy individuals, acquired during rest on a Siemens Biograph mMR 3T PET-MR scanner from two independent cohorts:

1. A within-subject exploration cohort (TUM.exp) with nine participants was acquired across two sessions, one with their eyes open and the other with their eyes closed (mean age = 43 years, std = 7 years; 4 females).
2. A prospective replication cohort (TUM.rep) with eleven participants acuired with their eyes open (mean age = 27 years, std = 5 years; 6 females).

 Additionally, blood radioactivity was measured every second through automatic sampling from the radial artery with a Twilite blood sampler.

time.Description: Time in relation to time zero defined by the _pet.json

plasma_radioactivity.Description: Blood activity was measured by the Twilite Two blood detector, converted to plasma concentration using the b2plasma function from the Turku PET Center library (tpcc), modeled as a sum of exponentials using the function fit_feng (tpcc), and the model was evaluated in the middle of the reconstructed PET time-frames using the function fit2dat (tpcc).
